{"to":["sarah@helpinghandsunited.org"],"subject":"Community Care Day – Final Details & Notion Link","body":"Hi Sarah,

I hope you’re doing well. Below are the most up-to-date details for our joint Community Care Day. Everything is also collected in one place on Notion if you prefer to pull directly from there.

Notion Workspace (read-only link): https://www.notion.so/Community-Care-Day-Planning-20d0dc8fa0db815fac71c8264cc858e3

Key Details
• Date & Time: Saturday, March 15 | 10:00 AM – 4:00 PM  
  – Setup: 8:00 AM – 10:00 AM  
  – Cleanup: 4:00 PM – 5:30 PM
• Location: St. Mary’s Parish Hall & Grounds (123 Main St.)

Run-of-Show (working draft)
10:00 AM   Opening welcome & prayer (John)  
10:15 AM   Clothing/food distribution & health clinic open  
12:00 PM   Community lunch service  
1:00 PM    Job-fair booths & family activities begin  
3:15 PM    Closing remarks & thank-yous  
4:00 PM    Public programming ends | teardown begins

Volunteer Roles & Sign-Up
Hospitality/greeters, food-service line, clinic support, job-fair liaison, kids’ activity helpers, setup/cleanup crew.  
Sign-up sheet is embedded on the Notion page above (feel free to share that link in your message).

Talking Points / Highlights
• “Neighbors helping neighbors” – a day of practical care & fellowship.  
• Free health screenings, résumé help & local hiring opportunities.  
• Hot meal served to all guests.  
• Collaboration between faith community, nonprofits & area businesses.

Sponsor / Partner Acknowledgments  
• Helping Hands United  
• St. Mary’s Parish  
• Mercy Community Health Clinic  
• Downtown Business Association  
(High-resolution logos are stored in the “Media Assets” section of the Notion workspace.)

Day-Of Coordination Contacts  
• John – mobile ###-###-####  
• Sarah – mobile ###-###-####

Let me know if you need anything tightened up or if other details would be helpful. Happy to adjust as you prepare the wider email.

Blessings,
John
St. Mary’s Parish"}
